# Projocalypse documentation

**On fundamental changes** (commands, schema, features, stack, styling): update docs in the same delivery — see **`projocalypse-docs-sync.mdc`** (always apply).

## Start here

- [README.md](../../README.md) — features, commands, tech stack, data storage
- Cursor setup: [.cursor/README.md](../README.md)

## Terminology

- **Projocalypse** — browser-only project management app (Asana-inspired workflow)
- **Project** — top-level container with color, sections, and tasks
- **Section** — column/group within a project (default: To Do, In Progress, Done)
- **Task** — work item with title, description, due date, priority, completion
- **Subtask** — checklist item inside a task detail panel
- **My Tasks** — cross-project view of incomplete tasks
- **Export backup** — JSON file `projocalypse-backup-YYYY-MM-DD.json`, `ExportData` version `2` (developers + assignees; v1 still imports)
- **Developer** — team member scoped to a project (`projectId`); Master/Developer roles and permissions
- **Embed / host project** — fixed `hostProjectId` when mounted in Talemail or similar; see `doc/EMBED.md`

## When editing features or stack

- Keep README **Features** and **Getting started** sections accurate when behavior or commands change.
- New user-facing capability → add to README Features list in the same PR.
- Test commands belong in README **Tests** section; ship gate is `pnpm test:pr` per **`projocalypse-feature-ship.mdc`**.

## Doc layout and naming

- All directories under `doc/` MUST be **CAPITALIZED** (e.g. `PLAN`, `ADR`).
- All markdown files under `doc/` MUST use **CAPITALIZED** filenames (UPPER-KEBAB or UPPERCASE; e.g. `ROADMAP.md`, `README.md`).
- Place new docs in the appropriate CAPITALIZED subdir (`PLAN` for planning, `ADR` for decision records if added later).

Matches **`projocalypse-filenames.mdc`**. Embed contract: [doc/EMBED.md](../../doc/EMBED.md).

## Repo note

Do not invent features, schema fields, or commands not reflected in README or `src/` unless you are explicitly adding them with matching doc updates in the same task.
